South African Credit Growth Slowed to 5.1% in March From 5.4% in February

-- B y   N a s r e e n   S e r i a
-- 
2011-04-29T06:02:15Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-29/south-african-credit-growth-slowed-to-5-1-in-march-from-5-4-in-february.html
South African credit growth slowed
to an annual 5.1 percent in March from 5.4 percent in February,
the central bank said.  The median estimate of eight economists surveyed by
Bloomberg was for credit to rise 5.9 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nasreen Seria in Johannesburg at 
 nseria@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Alastair Reed at 
 areed12@bloomberg.net  